[In the past 24 hours, 13 countries including the USA (74 975), India (31 291), UK (28 856), Philippines (26 251), Turkey (22 923), Malaysia (19 550), Russia (18 891), Iran (16 654), Brazil (14 314), Thailand (14 029), Mexico (12 511), Viet Nam (11 932), and Israel (11 396) have reported the highest numbers of cases, all reporting more than 10 000 newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours. A global total of 7731 deaths were reported in the past 24 hours (late 9 Sep 2021 to late 10 Sep 2021). There appears to be the customary weekend-related drop in the reported case numbers. A total of 56 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours; 30 of the 56 countries are from the European region, 7 are from the Americas region, 6 are from the Eastern Mediterranean region, 5 are from the South East Asia region, 6 are from the Western Pacific region, and 2 are from the African region.

Comparing the 7-day averages of daily confirmed cases from the past 7 days and those from 8-14 days ago, case counts have decreased by 9.8%, while daily reported deaths have decreased by 6.8%. Similar comparative 7-day averages in the USA show a 9.9% decrease in daily reported cases and 5.1% increase in reported deaths.

Impression: The global daily reported approximately 450 000 newly confirmed infections in the past 24 hours with over 225.09 million cumulative reported cases and over 4.63 million reported deaths. - Mod.UBA]
